<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1925-02-06T08:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1925-02-06T08:00:00-05:00" n="135" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d135">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">463.00 R 29/166: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in France</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Whitehouse</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-02-06T13:00:00+00:00"><hi rend="italic">February 6,
                                        1925—1 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received February 6—11:40
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>108. My 75, January 21, 3 p.m. British memorandum was adopted by the
                            Conference this morning, subject to my reservation that I had as yet
                            received no instructions.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Whitehouse</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
